    "discriminators": [
     "MOVEMENT-PRESENCE < MOVEMENT-CROWD < MOVEMENT-ACTIVITY is an explicit UCS DENSITY/LEVEL CONTINUUM, not three different sources. The ordered axes are onset_rate_per_second, root_mean_square_level and lufs: PRESENCE ~0.8 onsets/s at ~-34 LUFS; CROWD ~4 onsets/s at ~-26 LUFS; ACTIVITY ~10 onsets/s at ~-19 LUFS. The three sets of priors are deliberately non-overlapping at one deviation - this is one of the cleanest signal cases in UCS.",
     "The TOP: crowds moving AND handling objects - cleaning, moving boxes, shopping. The densest and loudest of the three, and the only one with a MIXED onset population (footfalls plus object impacts), which shows up as higher spectral_flux, higher spectral_centroid_hz and even lower onset_periodicity than CROWD.",
     "Against MOVEMENT-CROWD: about 2.5x the onset_rate_per_second and ~7 LUFS louder. If it is only feet, it is CROWD.",
     "Still no vocals (UCS: 'clean recordings with no vocals') - voicing_ratio near zero."
    ],
